examples.en: The needle pierced her skin.
Her eyes pierced into him.
examples.ru: Она вперила в него свой взгляд.

examples.en: The arrow pierced his back.
She's had her ears pierced.
The bullet pierced his lung.
A scream pierced the silence.
The scream pierced the night.
I had my belly-button pierced.
examples.ru: Я проколола пупок. / Я сделала пирсинг на пупке.

examples.en: The needle pierced into her skin.
Light pierced through the forest.
The cold wind pierced our clothes.
A sudden scream pierced the silence.
Her memories sometimes pierced her heart.
The door was thirled or pierced in many places.
examples.ru: Дверь была продырявлена во многих местах.

examples.en: Their tears pierced the hearts of their pitying neighbors.
examples.ru: Их слёзы пронзали сердца их жалостливых соседей.

examples.en: Their new album pierced through convention and the status quo.
examples.ru: Их новый альбом проложил себе дорогу сквозь условности и обыденность.

examples.en: The knife had pierced his heart, but incredibly he was still alive.
examples.ru: Нож пронзил его сердце, но — невероятно — он был ещё жив.

examples.en: From atop his horse the warrior hurled a javelin that pierced the chest of his hapless foe.
examples.ru: Сидя на своём коне, воин метнул копьё, которое пронзило грудь его незадачливого врага.

examples.en: The cold pierced her bones.
The needle pierced her flesh.
The bullet pierced through his lung.
The men's lanterns pierced through the dense mist.
examples.ru: Свет фонарей мужчин пронзил густой туман.

examples.en: The spike pierced the receipts and held them in order.
examples.ru: Подставка для накалывания чеков позволяла содержать их в порядке.
